<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="worn-adj">worn <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /wɔːn/    美 /wɔːrn/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>用旧的；穿坏的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>two worn armchairs 
两把破旧的扶手椅</p><footer>外研⑦ – 2</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a worn sweater
穿旧的毛衣</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.<strong>疲倦的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a worn face 
一脸倦容</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="worn-out">worn out</h3>
<p>1.<strong>破旧的；筋疲力尽的(exhausted)：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>It’s a very old watch and is quite worn out. 
这是一块旧表，破旧不堪。</p><footer>2009 湖南</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I was worn out after a day of shopping. 
逛了一天商店，我都累坏了。</p></div></div>